{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "<div><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">The purpose of this course is to provide the students with the knowledge and skills to work as a professional in charge of pricing decisions and revenue management (RM). In particular, students are expected to be capable of managing both the qualitative and quantitative aspects of the business practices in the sectors heavily relying on RM, such as airlines, railways, and hospitality industries.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br /></div>", "到達目標": "<div><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Students will be able to:</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">•<span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span>Comprehend the fundamental knowledge and concepts critical to pricing and revenue management (RM) decisions</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">•<span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span>Perform the analysis of pricing and RM practices</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">•<span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span>Develop the skills of formulating and applying RM models</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">•<span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span>Identify, define, and handle real-world pricing and RM problems</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">•<span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span>Understand and prepare for the rising RM practical issues</span></div>", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "<div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">•<span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span>Pricing basics and applications</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">•<span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span>Special pricing problems</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">•<span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span>Revenue Management (RM) background and concepts</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">•<span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span>RM techniques and models</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">•<span style=\"w